<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="48" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,158,725]" pageId="6" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,274,158,184]" pageId="6" pageNumber="48">Description</emphasis>
:—LM (
<figureCitation box="[370,504,158,184]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–31" captionStartId="5.[136,243,853,875]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,461,829]" captionTargetId="figure-118@5.[151,1435,461,829]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 19–31. Stauroneis dharwarensis Wadmare &amp; B.Karthick nom. nov., stat. nov., 19. Original illustration of Gandhi (1959a: 104, 105, Fig. 25). 20–31. Light micrographs (DIC) from the type material (AHMA Sr 48), Fig. 24 represents the lectotype. Scale bar = 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6875625" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6875625/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="48">Figs 19–31</figureCitation>
): Valves broadly lanceolate with constricted, subrostrate to rostrate apices. Length 32.0–64.0 µm, breadth 12.0–15.0 µm. Axial area narrow, widening at centre. Stauros bow-tie shaped, widening towards valve margin. Raphe slightly coarse with straight central raphe ends, terminal raphe fissures unilaterally deflected. Striae strongly radial punctate, 17–19/10 µm. Areolae punctate to transapically elongated, discernible in LM. (n= 36).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,158,725]" pageId="6" pageNumber="48">
SEM (
<figureCitation box="[261,393,338,364]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 32–36" captionStart-1="FIGURES 37–41" captionStartId-0="5.[136,243,1981,2003]" captionStartId-1="7.[136,243,1041,1063]" captionTargetBox-0="[237,1350,973,1956]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1435,190,1017]" captionTargetId-0="figure-170@5.[237,1350,973,1956]" captionTargetId-1="figure-24@7.[151,1435,190,1017]" captionTargetPageId-0="5" captionTargetPageId-1="7" captionText-0="FIGURES 32–36. Stauroneis dharwarensis Wadmare &amp; B.Karthick nom. nov., stat. nov., SEM, external valve views. 32, 36. External views of an entire valve. 33. Stauros with tear-drop central raphe ends. 34, 35. Deflected terminal raphe fissures. Scale bars = 4 µm (Figs 32–36)." captionText-1="FIGURES 37–41. Stauroneis dharwarensis Wadmare &amp; B.Karthick nom. nov., stat. nov., SEM, internal valve views. 37, 38. Internal views of an entire valve. 37, 39.Apices showing terminal raphe fissures as helictoglossae. 40. Stauros thick bearing deflected central raphe ends. 39–41. Areolae with hymen layer. Scale bars = 4 µm (Figs 37–41)." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6875629" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6875631" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6875629/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6875631/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="48">Figs 32–41</figureCitation>
): Externally (
<figureCitation box="[542,672,338,364]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–36" captionStartId="5.[136,243,1981,2003]" captionTargetBox="[237,1350,973,1956]" captionTargetId="figure-170@5.[237,1350,973,1956]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 32–36. Stauroneis dharwarensis Wadmare &amp; B.Karthick nom. nov., stat. nov., SEM, external valve views. 32, 36. External views of an entire valve. 33. Stauros with tear-drop central raphe ends. 34, 35. Deflected terminal raphe fissures. Scale bars = 4 µm (Figs 32–36)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6875629" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6875629/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="48">Figs 32–36</figureCitation>
), valves linear-lanceolate with axial area narrow throughout but wider at centre (
<figureCitation box="[251,387,374,400]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–36" captionStartId="5.[136,243,1981,2003]" captionTargetBox="[237,1350,973,1956]" captionTargetId="figure-170@5.[237,1350,973,1956]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 32–36. Stauroneis dharwarensis Wadmare &amp; B.Karthick nom. nov., stat. nov., SEM, external valve views. 32, 36. External views of an entire valve. 33. Stauros with tear-drop central raphe ends. 34, 35. Deflected terminal raphe fissures. Scale bars = 4 µm (Figs 32–36)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6875629" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6875629/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="48">Figs 32, 36</figureCitation>
