). Terminal raphe fissures terminating onto helictoglossae (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 37–41" captionStartId="7.[136,243,1041,1063]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,190,1017]" captionTargetId="figure-24@7.[151,1435,190,1017]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 37–41. Stauroneis dharwarensis Wadmare &amp; B.Karthick nom. nov., stat. nov., SEM, internal valve views. 37, 38. Internal views of an entire valve. 37, 39.Apices showing terminal raphe fissures as helictoglossae. 40. Stauros thick bearing deflected central raphe ends. 39–41. Areolae with hymen layer. Scale bars = 4 µm (Figs 37–41)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6875631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6875631/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="48">Figs 38, 39</figureCitation>
). Striae radiate, areolae with hymen occlusions (
<figureCitation box="[753,884,518,544]" captionStart="FIGURES 37–41" captionStartId="7.[136,243,1041,1063]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,190,1017]" captionTargetId="figure-24@7.[151,1435,190,1017]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 37–41. Stauroneis dharwarensis Wadmare &amp; B.Karthick nom. nov., stat. nov., SEM, internal valve views. 37, 38. Internal views of an entire valve. 37, 39.Apices showing terminal raphe fissures as helictoglossae. 40. Stauros thick bearing deflected central raphe ends. 39–41. Areolae with hymen layer. Scale bars = 4 µm (Figs 37–41)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6875631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6875631/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="48">Figs 39–41</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
